==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} [[pronominal adverb]] {{term|therfore|lang=ang}}; see {{term|there}}, {{term|fore}}, and {{term|for}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈðɛəfɔː/}}, {{SAMPA|/"DE@fO:/}}
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|/ˈðɛɹfɔɹ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"DErfOr/}}
* {{audio|en-us-therefore.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{hyphenation|there|fore}}
* {{homophones|therefor}} (second syllable stressed)

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{context|conjunctive}} For that or this purpose, referring to something previously stated.
#* {{RQ:Authorized Version|Luke|14|20}}
#*: I have married a wife, and '''therefore''' I can not come.
#* {{RQ:Authorized Version|Matthew|19|27}}
#*: Behold, we have forsaken all, and followed thee; what shall we have '''therefore'''?
# {{context|conjunctive}} [[consequently|Consequently]], by or in consequence of that or this cause; referring to something previously stated.
#* {{rfdate}}, Spectator
#*: He blushes; '''therefore''' he is guilty.

